{"commentv2": 1, "number": 0, "id": 2281516, "nreplies": 0, "sticky": 0, "user": "Reignac", "body": "You may know Rehgar from HotS, but that's not where he was originally from. He first showed up in the comic books.\n\nRehgar was raised by ogres on Draenor as a gladiator, and come adulthood he had a gladiator team of his own: the blood elf rogue [url=http://legion.wowhead.com/npc=98102/valeera-sanguinar]Valeera Sanguinar[/url], night elf druid [url=http://legion.wowhead.com/npc=105931/broll-bearmantle]Broll Bearmantle[/url], and a human warrior with amnesia named Lo'Gosh. Now Rehgar was technically their slave master, but he cared for them, healing them after every match and keeping them on a long leash. When they ran away  to get Lo'Gosh's memories back, he didn't bother to go after them and retired from the job instead.\n\nNext time we saw Rehgar he was one of [url=http://legion.wowhead.com/npc=4949/thrall]Thrall's[/url] advisers and joined the Warchief at a Theramore peace conference, where the Horde was meeting with [url=http://legion.wowhead.com/npc=29611/king-varian-wrynn]Varian Wrynn[/url], his old gladiator Lo'Gosh who had gotten his memory back. In Cataclysm, Rehgar joined the Earthen Ring at the Maelstrom.", "date": "2015-11-28T15:36:56-06:00", "rating": 13, "indent": 0, "roles": 256, "deleted": 0, "outofdate": 0, "userRating": 0, "replies": [], "dataTree": 1, "markupDisabledEnvironments": {"ptr": true, "beta": false}, "lastEdit": ["2016-02-27T16:39:50-06:00", 2, "Reignac"]}
